==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Itinerancy
<hw>I*tin"er*an*cy</hw> <pr>(⟦isl⟧*t⟦icr⟧n"⟦etil⟧r*⟦ait⟧n*s⟦ycr⟧)</pr>,1
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Itinerant</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A passing from place to place.</def> <rj><au>Dr. H.
More.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A discharge of official duty involving frequent
change of residence; the custom or practice of discharging official duty
in this way; also, a body of persons who thus discharge official
duty.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Itinerant</ent>⟦br⟧
